Jesse Brown is a professional rodeo contestant specializing in steer wrestling, also known as bulldogging. Born in Baker City, Oregon, Brown initially pursued football, playing as a quarterback at Washington State University before transferring to Montana State University to focus on rodeo.

He joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2016 and was named the steer wrestling rookie of the year in 2017.

Here you can follow Jesse Brown’s net worth, career earnings, earnings, biography, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Jesse Brown

Jesse Brown was born in the early 1990s in Baker City, Oregon, USA. His parents, Jim and Vicki Brown, come from ranching backgrounds.

His father, Jim Brown, was a professional saddle bronc rider. Jesse’s younger sister Allie is a barrel racer and breakaway roper.

Early Career

Before his rodeo career, Brown was a standout athlete in high school, particularly in football. He initially enrolled at Washington State University, where he played football for three years.

However, he eventually transferred to Montana State University, where he joined the rodeo team and qualified for the College National Finals Rodeo.

Professional Career

Jesse Brown joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2016 and quickly made a name for himself.

He was named the PRCA’s Steer Wrestling Rookie of the Year in 2017. Since then, he has continued to excel in the sport, qualifying for the National Finals Rodeo multiple times.

In 2023, he won the Clark County Fair & Rodeo in Logandale, Nevada, and the Cinch Playoff Series Championship in Sioux Falls, South Dakota.

Jesse Brown’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Jesse Brown’s net worth is estimated to be $1.5 million.

His earnings from his successful rodeo career, including his winnings from various competitions, contribute to his overall income.

Career Earnings

Over the years, Jesse Brown has earned significant income from his rodeo career. For instance, in 2017, he ranked 82nd in the World Standings with earnings of $15,501.

In 2018, he earned $44,153, and in 2019, his earnings increased to $51,921. In 2020, he earned $88,559.

Endorsements

Brown has several endorsements, as seen on his Instagram profile. He is endorsed by brands such as Resistol, CSI Saddle Pads, Cinch Jeans, DUBA Trailers, Rascal Rodeo, Vetericyn, and GastroSnax.

Personal Details

Girlfriend

Steer wrestler Jesse’s gorgeous girlfriend is Gracie. The couple shares beautiful pictures on Instagram.

How Old is Jesse Brown?

He is 31 years old as of November 2023.

How tall is he?

He is 6 ft 2 inches.

What is his nationality?

He is an American.

Career Highlights

  • Career earnings: $607,492
  • 2022 world standings place: 5th
  • 2022 Wrangler NFR standings place: 2nd   
  • 2022 Wrangler NFR earnings: $149,439
  • 2022 earnings: $241,152
  • Wrangler NFR Qualifications: 3 (2020-22)

2023 Highlights

• Won the San Antonio (Texas) Stock Show & Rodeo

• Won the Clark County Fair & Rodeo (Logandale, Nev.)

• Won the Medicine Hat (Alberta) Stampede

• Won the Jerome (Idaho) County Fair And Rodeo

• Won the Cinch Playoff Series Championship (Sioux Falls, S.D.)

• Co-champion at the Lynden (Wash.) PRCA Rodeo

FAQs About Jesse Brown

$1.5 million.

When did he start his rodeo career?

He started his professional rodeo career in 2016 when he joined the PRCA.

Who are his endorsers?

Brown is endorsed by several brands, including Resistol, CSI Saddle Pads, Cinch Jeans, DUBA Trailers, Rascal Rodeo, Vetericyn, and GastroSnax.
